  {title:'WWDC 2026: Safari 27 Beta — CSS Grid Masonry + Customisable Select',tier:'s',tierLabel:'S Tier',pipeline:'Webflow Build → QA',source:'WebKit Blog',url:'https://webkit.org/blog/17967/news-from-wwdc26-webkit-in-safari-27-beta/',benefit:'Native masonry layouts and fully styleable dropdowns just landed in Safari 27 beta — two of the most-requested CSS features for client builds, now without JavaScript.',roi:'Immediate',fit:5,why:'Safari 27 beta launched at WWDC 2026 with 58 new features. CSS Grid Lanes give you Pinterest-style waterfall layouts in pure CSS with no JS library. Customisable select lets you style native dropdowns to match brand using `::picker()` — no more rebuilding them in JavaScript and losing native accessibility.',steps:['Test `grid-template-rows: masonry` in a Webflow custom code block — Safari 27 beta is available in developer settings today.','Prototype a brand-styled `<select>` using `::picker()` pseudo-element — replace the JS select library on one active client site.','Gate both with `@supports` for now — Chrome Grid Masonry support is expected in Chrome 150+.'],impl:{Research:'1h',Build:'3h',QA:'2h',Rollout:'1h',Total:'7h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'+15%'},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'+10%'},'Page Perf':{val:'+8%'}},compat:{Webflow:'Partial',Figma:'No',n8n:'No',Cloudflare:'No',Playwright:'Yes','Website QA':'Yes'}},
  {title:'Figma Check Designs + Make Local Codebase Connection',tier:'a',tierLabel:'A Tier',pipeline:'Figma → Webflow Build',source:'Figma Release Notes',url:'https://www.figma.com/release-notes/',benefit:'"Check Designs" catches WCAG failures and library mismatches before handoff — and Figma Make now edits your actual Git repo and opens PRs directly from Figma.',roi:'High',fit:5,why:'"Check Designs" compares every frame against your design system in one click: WCAG AA contrast failures, detached components, and library mismatches all surface before anything reaches dev. Figma Make\'s local codebase connection (closed beta, May 28) takes it further — design change in Figma, code edit committed, PR opened, all without a terminal.',steps:['Enable Check Designs on an active client Figma file and run it before the next handoff — fix all WCAG AA contrast failures before passing to dev.','Apply for Figma Make closed beta access via the release notes page.','Add "Check Designs passed" as a required sign-off step in the project handoff checklist.'],impl:{Research:'1h',Build:'1h',QA:'1h',Rollout:'1h',Total:'4h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'+20%'},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'+25%'},'Page Perf':{val:'—',neutral:true}},compat:{Webflow:'No',Figma:'Yes',n8n:'No',Cloudflare:'No',Playwright:'No','Website QA':'Yes'}},
  {title:'TLS Client Certificate Sunset — June 15 Deadline',tier:'a',tierLabel:'A Tier',pipeline:'10-Template → Client Handoff',source:'SSL Calendar',url:'https://sslcalendar.com/blog/public-tls-client-certificates-phased-out-2026/',benefit:'Chrome stops trusting publicly-issued client certificates on June 15 — check any B2B or enterprise client using certificate-based auth before it breaks silently.',roi:'Immediate',fit:3,why:'From June 15 2026, major browsers no longer accept publicly trusted TLS client authentication certificates. Rare in consumer sites, but B2B and enterprise clients in finance, healthcare, and government commonly use cert-based auth. Failures will be immediate and silent from the user\'s perspective.',steps:['Email every enterprise or B2B client asking whether they use client certificate authentication — one message surfaces the risk.','For any affected client, migrate to OAuth 2.0 or SAML before June 15.','Add a client certificate auth question to the new project intake form for enterprise clients.'],impl:{Research:'1h',Build:'3h',QA:'2h',Rollout:'1h',Total:'7h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'—',neutral:true},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'+5%'},'Page Perf':{val:'—',neutral:true}},compat:{Webflow:'No',Figma:'No',n8n:'No',Cloudflare:'Yes',Playwright:'No','Website QA':'Yes'}},
  {title:'Chrome 149 Stable — CSS Gap Decorations + bfcache for WebSocket Pages',tier:'a',tierLabel:'A Tier',pipeline:'Webflow Build → QA',source:'Chrome for Developers',url:'https://developer.chrome.com/blog/new-in-chrome-149',benefit:'Style grid and flex gaps directly in CSS — removes the last major layout workaround needed in Webflow custom code.',roi:'High',fit:4,why:'CSS gap decorations (Chrome 149 stable, June 2) let you draw lines, apply colours, and control insets inside the gaps of any CSS Grid or Flexbox layout using `column-rule-inset` and `row-rule-inset`. Until now this required negative margins or pseudo-elements. bfcache also now works on pages with active WebSockets — fixing back/forward navigation on chat or live-data client sites.',steps:['Audit the shared component library for any grid dividers using negative margins or pseudo-elements — replace with gap decorations.','Test `column-rule-inset` in a Webflow custom code block and add the pattern to the Webflow dev guide.','Verify bfcache eligibility for client pages using WebSockets via DevTools > Application > Back/Forward Cache.'],impl:{Research:'0.5h',Build:'2h',QA:'1h',Rollout:'0.5h',Total:'4h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'+10%'},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'+5%'},'Page Perf':{val:'+8%'}},compat:{Webflow:'Partial',Figma:'No',n8n:'No',Cloudflare:'No',Playwright:'Yes','Website QA':'Yes'}},
  {title:'Google I/O 2026: WebMCP Origin Trial Launches in Chrome 149',tier:'b',tierLabel:'B Tier',pipeline:'10-Template → Client Handoff',source:'Chrome for Developers',url:'https://developer.chrome.com/blog/chrome-at-io26',benefit:'WebMCP lets browser AI agents take structured actions on websites — register for the origin trial now before clients start asking you to implement it.',roi:'Medium',fit:3,why:'WebMCP (origin trial in Chrome 149) is a proposed open web standard that exposes JavaScript functions and HTML forms to browser-native AI agents. The idea: a user\'s AI agent can fill forms, trigger actions, and navigate your site programmatically via a structured tool interface. Sites designed for agent interaction will have an advantage when this goes mainstream.',steps:['Read the WebMCP spec overview — budget 1h for one team member this week.','Register for the Chrome 149 origin trial to start testing on one project.','Identify which client sites have forms or actions that would benefit from agent-accessible markup — document for future proposals.'],impl:{Research:'2h',Build:'—',QA:'—',Rollout:'—',Total:'2h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'—',neutral:true},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'—',neutral:true},'Page Perf':{val:'—',neutral:true}},compat:{Webflow:'Partial',Figma:'No',n8n:'No',Cloudflare:'No',Playwright:'No','Website QA':'No'}},
  {title:'n8n — Notion OAuth + Alibaba Cloud Chat Model Node',tier:'b',tierLabel:'B Tier',pipeline:'n8n Automation → Client Delivery',source:'n8n Docs',url:'https://docs.n8n.io/release-notes/',benefit:'n8n now supports Notion OAuth natively — remove hard-coded Notion API tokens from client automation workflows.',roi:'Medium',fit:4,why:'n8n\'s latest June release adds native Notion OAuth credential support, so workflows reading or writing to Notion no longer need integration tokens managed manually. Also ships: an Alibaba Cloud Chat Model node for lower-cost AI model evaluation, webhook caching performance improvements, and a sweep of stability fixes from the May regression cycle.',steps:['Migrate any n8n workflows using Notion API tokens to the new OAuth credential type — takes 15 minutes per workflow.','Test the Alibaba Cloud Chat Model node if you are evaluating cost alternatives to OpenAI for client automation.','Apply all recent n8n patches — the May/June release cycle included 5+ stability fixes worth picking up.'],impl:{Research:'0.5h',Build:'1h',QA:'0.5h',Rollout:'0.5h',Total:'2.5h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'+10%'},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'+5%'},'Page Perf':{val:'—',neutral:true}},compat:{Webflow:'Yes',Figma:'No',n8n:'Yes',Cloudflare:'No',Playwright:'No','Website QA':'Partial'}},
  {title:'Cloudflare Browser Run — Live View + 4x Higher Concurrency',tier:'b',tierLabel:'B Tier',pipeline:'QA → Website QA',source:'Cloudflare Blog',url:'https://www.cloudflare.com/agents-week/updates/',benefit:'Cloudflare\'s serverless browser service now supports live view, session recordings, and 4x more concurrent sessions — cloud-based Playwright testing is now practical for agency QA.',roi:'Medium',fit:3,why:'Cloudflare renamed Browser Rendering to "Browser Run" during Agents Week and added a live view dashboard, session recordings, CDP access, and raised concurrency from 2 to 8 simultaneous browsers. Also ships: Cloudflare Workflows saga-style rollbacks where each step can define compensating logic for downstream failures.',steps:['Test Cloudflare Browser Run as a CI step for Website QA — run a standard Playwright audit against one client staging URL.','Evaluate session recordings for capturing client-facing bug reproductions without setting up a separate tool.','Compare cost and concurrency vs running Playwright on GitHub Actions workers for the same workload.'],impl:{Research:'1h',Build:'2h',QA:'1h',Rollout:'1h',Total:'5h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'+5%'},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'+20%'},'Page Perf':{val:'—',neutral:true}},compat:{Webflow:'Yes',Figma:'No',n8n:'Yes',Cloudflare:'Yes',Playwright:'Yes','Website QA':'Yes'}},
  {title:'Microsoft Record Patch Tuesday — 208 CVEs Including 3 Zero-Days',tier:'c',tierLabel:'C Tier',pipeline:'Client Handoff → Reporting',source:'Krebs on Security',url:'https://krebsonsecurity.com/2026/06/a-record-breaking-patch-tuesday-for-june-2026/',benefit:'The largest Patch Tuesday ever — 33 critical flaws and 3 publicly exploited zero-days. Apply Windows Update on all agency machines and Azure-hosted infrastructure today.',roi:'Immediate',fit:2,why:'Microsoft patched 208 vulnerabilities on June 9 2026 — the largest single Patch Tuesday in recorded history. 33 were critical, 55 involved remote code execution, and 3 were already being actively exploited. Primarily Windows and Office, but any Azure-hosted client infrastructure is in scope.',steps:['Apply Windows Update on all agency development machines immediately — do not defer this cycle.','Check Azure-hosted client infrastructure for affected services — prioritise anything flagged as RCE exposure.','Include this in the June client security summary if you send a monthly infrastructure report.'],impl:{Research:'0.5h',Build:'—',QA:'0.5h',Rollout:'1h',Total:'2h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'—',neutral:true},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'—',neutral:true},'Page Perf':{val:'—',neutral:true}},compat:{Webflow:'No',Figma:'No',n8n:'No',Cloudflare:'Yes',Playwright:'No','Website QA':'No'}}
