  {title:'Webflow AEO Launches at Google I/O — First Agency to Offer This Wins the Quarter',tier:'s',tierLabel:'S Tier',pipeline:'SEO → Content Strategy',source:'Webflow Updates',url:'https://webflow.com/feature/aeo',benefit:'Webflow just launched the first built-in Answer Engine Optimisation product — agencies that pitch this before competitors even know it exists have a real window.',roi:'Immediate',fit:5,why:'Announced at Google I/O 2026 (May 19-20) and launched May 21, Webflow AEO measures how a client\'s brand appears in ChatGPT, Perplexity, and Gemini answers and gives AI-assisted recommendations to improve that visibility. Clients are already asking why they\'re not in AI answers. Now there\'s a native tool inside the platform you already use to answer that.',steps:['Enable AEO on the agency\'s own Webflow site immediately — generate a visibility baseline to use in sales conversations.','Build a one-page AEO Audit deliverable: AI search visibility score, top content gaps, and 3 schema recommendations.','Reach out to 3 existing SEO retainer clients this week and offer an AEO audit as a value-add to their current engagement.'],impl:{Research:'1h',Build:'2h',QA:'1h',Rollout:'2h',Total:'6h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'—',neutral:true},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'—',neutral:true},'Page Perf':{val:'+15%'}},compat:{Webflow:'Yes',Figma:'No',n8n:'Yes',Cloudflare:'No',Playwright:'No','Website QA':'Yes'}},
  {title:'Google May 2026 Core Update — Rolling Out Now, Monitor Client Rankings Daily',tier:'s',tierLabel:'S Tier',pipeline:'SEO → Content Strategy',source:'Search Engine Journal',url:'https://www.searchenginejournal.com/google-begins-rolling-out-may-2026-core-update/575589/',benefit:'Google\'s second core update of 2026 is live as of May 21 and is the most impactful of the year — set up daily rank monitoring for all clients today.',roi:'Immediate',fit:5,why:'The May 2026 Core Update started May 21 and practitioners are calling it larger than the March update. The March update introduced holistic CWV scoring where failing one metric compounds the others — this update reinforces it. Sites with LCP above 2 seconds or CLS above 0.1 are at highest risk. The update typically takes 1-2 weeks to complete.',steps:['Set up daily rank tracking for the top 10 keywords on each active client site using Google Search Console Performance.','Run PageSpeed Insights on the 5 highest-traffic pages per client today to establish a pre-update CWV baseline.','Queue hero image AVIF conversion and `fetchpriority="high"` for the 3 clients with the weakest LCP scores — have fixes ready to deploy if rankings drop.'],impl:{Research:'1h',Build:'—',QA:'2h',Rollout:'3h',Total:'6h / site'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'—',neutral:true},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'—',neutral:true},'Page Perf':{val:'+20%'}},compat:{Webflow:'Yes',Figma:'No',n8n:'No',Cloudflare:'Yes',Playwright:'No','Website QA':'Yes'}},
  {title:'Figma Make Closed Beta Launches — AI Agent Connected to Your Codebase (May 28)',tier:'a',tierLabel:'A Tier',pipeline:'Figma → Webflow Build',source:'Figma Release Notes',url:'https://fig-events.figma.com/may-rn-2026/',benefit:'Figma Make connects directly to your Git repo — design change in Figma becomes a code edit, commit, and PR, without touching a terminal.',roi:'High',fit:4,why:'Figma Make (closed beta from May 28) connects to a local codebase via Figma MCP, lets you prompt code edits in natural language, and opens PRs from inside Figma. It also adds a Plan mode for multi-section layouts before generation. This directly targets the Figma-to-Next.js handoff workflow and will change how design-dev collaboration works when it opens broadly.',steps:['Apply for Figma Make closed beta access via the May release notes page.','When access is granted, test on a small headless project — make a design change in Figma and let Make generate the code change.','Document what it gets right and what needs manual correction — this becomes your positioning for how you present it to clients.'],impl:{Research:'1h',Build:'2h',QA:'1h',Rollout:'—',Total:'4h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'+25%'},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'+10%'},'Page Perf':{val:'—',neutral:true}},compat:{Webflow:'No',Figma:'Yes',n8n:'No',Cloudflare:'No',Playwright:'Yes','Website QA':'No'}},
  {title:'Google I/O 2026 — WebMCP, On-Device AI, and Modern Web Guidance Announced',tier:'a',tierLabel:'A Tier',pipeline:'10-Template → Client Handoff',source:'Chrome for Developers',url:'https://developer.chrome.com/blog/chrome-at-io26',benefit:'Google I/O packed 15 Chrome announcements into two days — WebMCP (AI agent standard), on-device Prompt API, and 100+ expert web coding patterns are the three that matter for the agency.',roi:'High',fit:3,why:'Google I/O 2026 (May 19-20) confirmed the Prompt API as stable (on-device Gemini Nano, no API cost), launched the WebMCP origin trial (AI agents interacting with websites via structured tools), and published Modern Web Guidance — 100+ expert-vetted coding patterns for performance, accessibility, and security to guide AI coding tools.',steps:['Watch the Chrome at I/O 2026 recording as a team (45 min) — identify any feature affecting current client projects.','Prototype the Prompt API on one Webflow or Next.js page — a FAQ chatbot or page summariser takes about 2h.','Register interest in the WebMCP origin trial in Chrome 149 for early access.'],impl:{Research:'2h',Build:'4h',QA:'1h',Rollout:'1h',Total:'8h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'+10%'},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'+5%'},'Page Perf':{val:'+10%'}},compat:{Webflow:'Partial',Figma:'No',n8n:'No',Cloudflare:'Yes',Playwright:'No','Website QA':'No'}},
  {title:'Google Maps — Heatmap Layer + Drawing Library Permanently Removed',tier:'a',tierLabel:'A Tier',pipeline:'Webflow Build → Client Handoff',source:'Google Maps Platform',url:'https://developers.google.com/maps/deprecations',benefit:'Two Google Maps API features were removed this month — any client site using them has broken map functionality right now and needs an urgent fix.',roi:'Immediate',fit:3,why:'`google.maps.visualization.HeatmapLayer` (deprecated May 2025) and the Drawing Library `google.maps.drawing.*` (deprecated August 2025) are now permanently unavailable and throw errors. Neither has a direct Maps API replacement — deck.gl is Google\'s recommended heatmap alternative.',steps:['Search all client codebases and Webflow embeds for `HeatmapLayer`, `google.maps.visualization`, and `google.maps.drawing` — any match is a broken feature.','Replace Heatmap Layer with deck.gl\'s HeatmapLayer or a static heatmap image depending on the client\'s traffic volume.','Add Google Maps feature deprecation checks to the annual client site audit checklist.'],impl:{Research:'1h',Build:'3h',QA:'1h',Rollout:'1h',Total:'6h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'—',neutral:true},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'+10%'},'Page Perf':{val:'—',neutral:true}},compat:{Webflow:'Partial',Figma:'No',n8n:'No',Cloudflare:'No',Playwright:'Yes','Website QA':'Yes'}},
  {title:'Playwright 1.60 Python Build Released — Drag-Drop Testing Now Cross-Language',tier:'b',tierLabel:'B Tier',pipeline:'QA → Website QA',source:'Playwright Docs',url:'https://playwright.dev/docs/release-notes',benefit:'Playwright 1.60 Python build (May 18) brings `locator.drop()` and improved ARIA error diagnostics to Python-based QA pipelines.',roi:'Medium',fit:3,why:'The Python build of Playwright 1.60 (May 18) brings the same features as the JS release from May 11: native `locator.drop()` for drag-and-drop testing, first-class HAR recording via `tracing.startHar()`, and `errorContext` that surfaces an ARIA snapshot in assertion failures — significantly cutting debugging time.',steps:['Upgrade the Playwright Python package: `pip install playwright --upgrade`.','Test `locator.drop()` against any client form upload zone or drag-and-drop CMS interface.','Update the QA test template to use `errorContext` ARIA snapshots in assertion failures — it reduces debugging time in CI.'],impl:{Research:'0.5h',Build:'1h',QA:'1h',Rollout:'0.5h',Total:'3h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'+5%'},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'+20%'},'Page Perf':{val:'—',neutral:true}},compat:{Webflow:'Yes',Figma:'No',n8n:'No',Cloudflare:'No',Playwright:'Yes','Website QA':'Yes'}},
  {title:'Webflow GitHub Sign-In Launches',tier:'c',tierLabel:'C Tier',pipeline:'Webflow Build → Client Handoff',source:'Webflow Updates',url:'https://webflow.com/updates/login-with-github',benefit:'Developers can now sign in to Webflow with GitHub — minor QoL improvement for teams context-switching between Webflow and GitHub repos.',roi:'Watch',fit:3,why:'Webflow added GitHub as a sign-in option on May 21. Reduces login friction for developers who already have GitHub SSO set up across their tools. Most useful for larger teams and anyone using Webflow Cloud alongside Git-connected headless projects. No change to client accounts.',steps:['Switch relevant agency team members to GitHub sign-in in Webflow account settings.','No action required for client accounts — this is a developer login option only.','Note: this does not connect Webflow to a GitHub repo — that is a separate Webflow Cloud feature.'],impl:{Research:'—',Build:'—',QA:'—',Rollout:'0.5h',Total:'0.5h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'+5%'},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'—',neutral:true},'Page Perf':{val:'—',neutral:true}},compat:{Webflow:'Yes',Figma:'No',n8n:'No',Cloudflare:'No',Playwright:'No','Website QA':'No'}},
  {title:'n8n Stability Patches — Multiple Releases Through Late May',tier:'c',tierLabel:'C Tier',pipeline:'n8n Automation → Client Delivery',source:'n8n Docs',url:'https://docs.n8n.io/release-notes/',benefit:'n8n shipped patches on May 20, 21, 25, 27, and 28 — update before end of month to pick up all webhook reliability and AI node fixes.',roi:'Watch',fit:4,why:'Five n8n releases in nine days points to a regression cycle following an earlier feature release. Fixes cover workflow execution edge cases, webhook reliability, and AI node stability. If any client automation workflows showed unexpected behaviour in May, one of these patches likely addresses it.',steps:['Update your self-hosted n8n instance to the latest stable release immediately.','Run active client workflows in a test environment after updating before promoting to production.','Review the n8n GitHub release notes for any changes touching workflows you maintain for clients.'],impl:{Research:'0.5h',Build:'—',QA:'1h',Rollout:'0.5h',Total:'2h'},impact:{'Build Speed':{val:'—',neutral:true},'QA Pass Rate':{val:'+5%'},'Page Perf':{val:'—',neutral:true}},compat:{Webflow:'Yes',Figma:'No',n8n:'Yes',Cloudflare:'No',Playwright:'No','Website QA':'No'}}
